        "client_msg_id": "9b775c86-b34d-46a2-86f0-42b7c631cd3a",
        "text": "I see two kinds of criticisms in your list:\n1. \"Figma-like canvas\" suggests visual editing and annotation, whereas Lem's visual canvas only does code-based visualization.\n2. Even for visualization, there is functionality I feel is missing.\nI don't see 2. as a valid criticism, given that this is very new and prototypy, meaning that more similar functionality is likely to be added in the near future. And you could probably add it yourself with reasonable effort.\n\nThe interesting question now is if the same can be said for 1. The author doesn't say anything about future plans. Is code visualization only the first step, or the only goal?\n\nCould you formulate your criticism as a suggestion, and submit it to the Lem's lead author?",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "e169f54bbaf8",
